  "Broker Comment" : "**12/2016 UPDATE: On November 17, 2016, the SEC issued an order approving Mr. Ruhl's application to associate as an representative with Hilliard Lyons pursuant to the conditions set forth in a heightened supervision plan.  Mr. Ruhl's registration with FINRA as well as the state of Indiana have both been approved.** /   IN ANTICIPATION OF THE INSTITUTION OF PROCEEDINGS, CITY AND RUHL SUBMITTED OFFERS OF SETTLEMENT WHICH THE COMMISSION ACCEPTED. WITHOUT ADMITTING OR DENYING THE FINDINGS, CITY AND RUHL CONSENTED TO THE ENTRY OF AN ORDER INSTITUTING ADMINISTRATIVE AND CEASE-AND-DESIST PROCEEDINGS PURSUANT TO SECTION 8A OF THE SECURITIES ACT OF 1933, SECTIONS 15(B) AND 21C OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934 AND SECTION 9(B) OF THE INVESTMENT COMPANY ACT OF 1940, MAKING FINDINGS AND IMPOSING REMEDIAL SANCTIONS AND A CEASE-AND-DESIST ORDER. RUHL WAS BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY BROKER, DEALER, INVESTMENT ADVISER, MUNICIPAL SECURITIES DEALER, MUNICIPAL ADVISOR, TRANSFER AGENT OR NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED STATISTICAL RATING ORGANIZATION - WITH THE RIGHT TO REAPPLY FOR RE-ENTRY AFTER ONE YEAR. RUHL WAS PERMANENTLY BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION IN A SUPERVISORY CAPACITY WITH ANY BROKER, DEALER, INVESTMENT ADVISER, MUNICIPAL SECURITIES DEALER, MUNICIPAL ADVISOR, TRANSFER AGENT OR NATIONALLY RECOGNIZED STATISTICAL RATING ORGANIZATION. RUHL WAS ORDERED TO PAY DISGORGEMENT OF $18,155, PREJUDGMENT INTEREST OF $2,165 AND A CIVIL MONEY PENALTY IN THE AMOUNT OF $18,155, ALL OF WHICH WAS PAID IN FULL ON AUGUST 2, 2013."
